WEBVTT

00:00.242 --> 00:03.544
<i>(ANNOUNCER) Previously, on
AMC's "Feed the Beast."</i>

00:03.646 --> 00:06.346
- I googled what happened to your mom.
<i>-(TIRES SCREECHING, GLASS SHATTERING)</i>

00:06.449 --> 00:09.750
Do you remember
anything?

00:09.853 --> 00:11.552
We'll need a third
of what you owe us.

00:11.654 --> 00:14.522
That's like...
$200,000.

00:14.624 --> 00:15.523
Talk to me!

00:15.625 --> 00:17.892
I can't help you
unless you say something!

00:19.796 --> 00:20.962
I'm reorganizing.

00:21.064 --> 00:24.398
The cop who put me away
is still meddling.

00:24.501 --> 00:26.100
Too rough.
I'll call Patrick.

00:26.202 --> 00:27.201
<i>It's not happenin'.</i>

00:27.303 --> 00:30.037
Something
has to be done.

00:32.525 --> 00:35.393
(FIRE CRACKLING)

00:35.429 --> 00:38.663
(MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING)

00:40.634 --> 00:44.402
(ROPE CREAKING)

00:46.000 --> 00:52.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:58.852 --> 01:01.886
(CELLPHONE VIBRATING)

01:07.628 --> 01:08.960
(VIBRATION STOPS)

01:09.898 --> 01:12.932
Hey, Dad. It's not like you
to be late for a meal.

01:12.967 --> 01:14.300
I'll see you soon, okay?

01:15.570 --> 01:17.136
(CELLPHONE THUDS)

01:17.171 --> 01:18.971
(BLUESY MUSIC PLAYING)

01:19.007 --> 01:22.441
(SEA BIRDS CALLING)

01:24.913 --> 01:26.646
Bullshit.

01:26.681 --> 01:29.015
Mr. Moran, sir.

01:29.050 --> 01:32.184
- Look, I just came to...
- To bullshit.

01:32.220 --> 01:34.754
(EXHALES) Look, it's just
an advance, you know?

01:34.789 --> 01:36.889
For... for Thirio.

01:36.925 --> 01:38.157
You don't need money
for the restaurant.

01:38.192 --> 01:39.492
Business is good.

01:39.527 --> 01:43.195
No, it's for some other crap
you got your dick stuck in.

01:43.231 --> 01:45.765
You really wanna know? Yeah.

01:45.800 --> 01:47.800
I'm in trouble. All right?

01:47.835 --> 01:50.002
I owe someone big-time.

01:50.038 --> 01:52.071
I've known you since
you were a boy.

01:52.106 --> 01:53.472
In all that time,

01:53.508 --> 01:55.775
there hasn't been a day
you <i> weren't</i> in trouble.

01:55.810 --> 01:57.576
I'll make it worth your while.

01:57.612 --> 02:00.079
Huh? It's like you said.
The restaurant's doing great,

02:00.114 --> 02:02.548
which means I can afford
to pay you back at a premium.

02:02.583 --> 02:04.350
I mean, that's on top
of your investment

02:08.523 --> 02:10.723
Believe it or not,

02:10.758 --> 02:12.525
I did not invest
in the restaurant

02:12.560 --> 02:14.427
because of your lamb chop.

02:14.462 --> 02:16.796
I did it for myself.

02:16.831 --> 02:18.597
And more importantly,
my grandson.

02:18.633 --> 02:21.701
(SWALLOWS, GROANS)

02:21.736 --> 02:24.170
So for once, Dion,

02:24.205 --> 02:26.272
you are not the center
of the universe.

02:28.543 --> 02:32.044
Now do you mind?

02:32.080 --> 02:33.312
Fine.

02:38.720 --> 02:40.052
(DOOR CLOSES)

02:40.088 --> 02:42.221
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

02:44.993 --> 02:46.359
Hey, Teej.

02:46.394 --> 02:48.928
I found these upstairs.
It's from your school.

02:48.963 --> 02:52.064
Do you have art
in this show?

02:52.100 --> 02:54.200
Well, it's tomorrow night.

02:54.235 --> 02:57.136
I can come, right?
I wanna see your artwork.

02:59.273 --> 03:00.573
- Hey.
- (DOOR CLOSES)

03:00.608 --> 03:03.109
- Where were you so early?
- Errands.

03:06.080 --> 03:08.314
Look, um,

03:08.349 --> 03:10.316
I know yesterday was
really intense

03:10.351 --> 03:11.717
for all of us.

03:11.753 --> 03:13.953
- (UTENSIL CLINKS)
- How you doing? Are you okay?

03:13.988 --> 03:18.391
You feeling...
sad about it?

03:19.694 --> 03:20.893
Scared?

03:23.331 --> 03:25.498
Okay.

03:25.533 --> 03:26.832
Do you feel guilty?

03:26.868 --> 03:29.602
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

03:29.637 --> 03:31.303
Hi, Mom!

03:31.339 --> 03:33.439
<i>-Hey, T.J.!
- (TIRES SQUEAL)</i>

03:33.474 --> 03:35.441
<i>-(RIE SCREAMS)
- No!</i>

03:37.011 --> 03:39.678
T.J., do you feel guilty?

03:44.752 --> 03:47.186
Well, I get that.
But you know what?

03:47.221 --> 03:50.022
You feeling guilty about
what happened to Andre?

03:50.058 --> 03:51.824
Means you care.

03:51.859 --> 03:54.460
You got a conscience,
a heart.

03:54.495 --> 03:56.028
That's a good thing.

03:58.733 --> 04:00.699
I love you.

04:00.735 --> 04:02.735
(KISSES, PATS BACK)

04:05.973 --> 04:08.374
(MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

04:11.913 --> 04:15.548
♪ Fever dream ♪

04:15.583 --> 04:18.184
♪ Or so it seems ♪

04:20.654 --> 04:22.221
♪ All I see is ♪

04:22.256 --> 04:24.623
♪ What used to be ♪

04:24.659 --> 04:27.460
♪ Fever dreams ♪

04:27.495 --> 04:31.263
♪ I've been around,
I'm lost and found ♪

04:31.299 --> 04:34.700
♪ I burned it all
to the ground ♪

04:34.735 --> 04:38.304
♪ Ashes to ashes,
hope that dashes ♪

04:38.339 --> 04:42.108
♪ My own new mystery ♪

04:42.143 --> 04:47.513
♪ And all I see
is what I used to be ♪

04:48.456 --> 04:51.136
- sync and corrections by Caio -
- www.addic7ed.com -

04:56.315 --> 05:00.417
Hey, how you doing, champ?
You okay?

05:00.452 --> 05:02.776
Hey, listen, on Monday,

05:02.800 --> 05:04.600
the kids all gonna be talking
about what happened.

05:04.635 --> 05:07.403
You know, people are gonna be
saying a lot of things.

05:07.438 --> 05:10.339
And your teachers...
Oh, and the teachers might

05:10.374 --> 05:12.141
even ask you
some questions.

05:12.176 --> 05:15.077
So you know what
you gotta do?

05:15.112 --> 05:17.146
All right.

05:17.181 --> 05:19.615
What's the capital
of Slovakia?

05:19.650 --> 05:21.483
Exactly. You don't know.

05:21.519 --> 05:23.552
You gotta pretend
like they just asked you,

05:23.587 --> 05:25.788
"What's the capital
of Slovakia?"

05:25.823 --> 05:27.790
And you don't know.

05:27.825 --> 05:30.359
All right, good man.

05:30.394 --> 05:33.395
(DISHES CLATTER)

05:35.666 --> 05:37.266
Hey.

05:37.301 --> 05:38.534
You gotta stop doing that.

05:38.569 --> 05:40.202
Doing what?

05:40.237 --> 05:41.937
The unsolicited parenting
thing.

05:41.972 --> 05:43.839
- Oh, come on. I was just trying to...
- That's not your call.

05:43.874 --> 05:45.441
You're gonna be a dad, right?

05:45.476 --> 05:48.343
How would you like it
if someone gave <i> your</i> kid advice

05:48.379 --> 05:50.212
that you totally
disagree with?

05:53.417 --> 05:56.785
(LOWERED VOICE)
All right. I'm sorry.

05:56.821 --> 05:58.287
(DISH CLATTERS)

06:01.025 --> 06:02.291
Yeah, what's this?

06:02.326 --> 06:04.860
Oh, what? You got an art show?

06:04.895 --> 06:05.894
Look at that.

06:05.930 --> 06:07.696
You want me to come to this?

06:07.731 --> 06:10.566
Yeah?

06:10.601 --> 06:12.000
Hey, you know what?

06:12.036 --> 06:13.702
You know, this is probably
something for you and your dad.

06:13.737 --> 06:15.537
Hey, but he's gonna tell me
all about it, right?

06:15.573 --> 06:17.339
- Yeah.
- Right.

06:19.510 --> 06:20.843
You know what?

06:20.878 --> 06:23.645
Um, I mean, if he wants you
to come, you should come.

06:27.985 --> 06:29.751
- You sure?
- Yeah.

06:30.888 --> 06:33.155
All right.

06:33.190 --> 06:34.656
All right. Yes.

06:34.692 --> 06:36.525
Thanks, man.

06:39.463 --> 06:40.829
DION: Hey.

06:43.667 --> 06:45.767
Hey. Morning.

06:45.803 --> 06:49.171
Hey. Morning.

06:49.206 --> 06:50.839
Are you okay?

06:50.875 --> 06:53.375
Yeah, I just don't know
what to do about T.J.

06:53.410 --> 06:54.943
I mean, he brings a gun
to school

06:54.979 --> 06:56.378
and there are
no consequences?

06:56.413 --> 06:58.180
What kind of life lesson
is that?

06:58.215 --> 07:00.215
- What happens when he's a teenager?
- Well, maybe he's...

07:00.251 --> 07:01.950
And Dion's solution
to everything

07:01.986 --> 07:03.719
is for him just to lie
to everyone.

07:05.122 --> 07:07.890
Maybe it'd be good for you
to step away from this

07:07.925 --> 07:09.324
for a little bit.

07:09.360 --> 07:13.295
You know, we could go grab
some coffee? Go for a walk?

07:13.330 --> 07:17.966
I mean, we've never actually
done either of those things.

07:18.002 --> 07:19.635
There's always something
going on.

07:19.670 --> 07:21.870
I know.

07:21.906 --> 07:24.740
So... coffee?

07:24.775 --> 07:26.108
I can't.

07:26.143 --> 07:28.076
I'm sorry. My brain's
about to explode.

07:28.112 --> 07:30.913
It wouldn't be fair to you.
Rain check?

07:30.948 --> 07:32.581
Sure.

07:39.623 --> 07:42.357
MARISA: Hi, Mom.
Hey, do you know where...

07:42.393 --> 07:43.926
What?

07:43.961 --> 07:45.627
What's the matter?

07:52.836 --> 07:55.370
The hell were you thinking?

07:55.406 --> 07:57.506
Leaving his body
where it could be found.

07:57.541 --> 07:59.308
You asked me to...

07:59.343 --> 08:02.144
I said I wanted the <i> Wloski</i> cop
disappeared,

08:02.179 --> 08:05.047
not put on display.

08:05.082 --> 08:07.883
You realize the heat
that's going to come down on us?

08:11.655 --> 08:13.488
(LOWERED VOICE)
Did you want him dead or not?

08:15.426 --> 08:19.962
When you <i> finally</i> carry out
an order, you screw it up.

08:19.997 --> 08:22.364
My own son!

08:22.399 --> 08:24.733
I teach you everything
since you were a boy,

08:24.768 --> 08:26.535
but I can't get through.

08:26.570 --> 08:28.804
Something is missing.

08:28.839 --> 08:30.672
You tell me, what is it?

08:32.208 --> 08:33.708
I... (INHALES DEEPLY)

08:33.744 --> 08:36.410
I don't know what you're...
(INHALES DEEPLY)

08:36.447 --> 08:37.980
What are you talking about?

08:38.015 --> 08:42.351
It is if you are compensating
for some defect of character.

08:42.385 --> 08:46.021
(MELODIC MUSIC PLAYING)

08:54.798 --> 08:58.367
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

09:02.973 --> 09:06.208
You son of a bitch.
You went through with it.

09:06.243 --> 09:10.345
Whoa. Hang on a second.
What are you talking about?

09:10.381 --> 09:12.080
The recording
on your voice mail.

09:12.116 --> 09:13.248
You plan to kill
Patrick Woijchik.

09:13.284 --> 09:14.750
All right, first of all,
that was not my plan.

09:14.785 --> 09:17.185
- It was the cop who wanted...
- That cop is dead.

09:19.690 --> 09:22.057
Dion, what did you do?

09:22.092 --> 09:25.427
Nothing.
G-Giordano... he called it off.

09:25.462 --> 09:26.762
- Besides, I'd...
- Then why is he dead?

09:26.797 --> 09:29.498
I don't know. I swear.

09:30.901 --> 09:34.936
Hey, look, why you so upset?

09:34.972 --> 09:37.539
This was bound to happen.
He was a dirty cop.

09:37.574 --> 09:39.675
Believe me, he was not
a good human being.

09:39.710 --> 09:42.244
- I mean, that guy was...
- Was my father.

09:44.682 --> 09:47.049
What?

09:47.084 --> 09:49.651
Guy...
Guy Giordano is your father?

09:51.188 --> 09:52.688
Was.

09:52.723 --> 09:54.456
Why didn't you tell me
when I played you the recording?

09:54.491 --> 09:55.524
Why didn't you say something?

09:55.559 --> 09:58.160
'Cause I was trying
to protect him.

09:58.195 --> 09:59.628
And I couldn't.

09:59.663 --> 10:01.963
I'm so, so sorry that you had to
go through something like this.

10:01.999 --> 10:03.899
You know, I-I know what
it's like to lose a parent.

10:03.934 --> 10:06.435
- I really do.
- Stop.

10:06.470 --> 10:08.937
I-I-I can't be around you.

10:08.972 --> 10:11.373
I have to be around people
that I can trust.

10:11.408 --> 10:12.974
Hey, hey. Come on, listen.

10:13.010 --> 10:15.477
Dion, no. Things just got
very real for me.

10:15.512 --> 10:18.013
And <i> this,</i> this is...

10:18.048 --> 10:20.315
This is not real.

10:20.351 --> 10:23.218
What's that supposed to mean?

10:23.253 --> 10:26.021
I have to keep my family safe.

10:28.926 --> 10:31.927
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING)

10:36.667 --> 10:38.233
(GRUNTS)

10:38.268 --> 10:39.768
You could buy a new one.

10:39.803 --> 10:41.903
Why? What's wrong with this?

10:41.939 --> 10:44.406
I'll hold in my stomach.

10:44.441 --> 10:47.442
Uncle, listen, I really need
to talk to you.

10:47.478 --> 10:48.910
I'm sorry. What the hell
is going on?

10:48.946 --> 10:50.645
We are getting married.

10:50.681 --> 10:51.847
What?

10:51.882 --> 10:53.115
Tasha needs a green card.

10:53.150 --> 10:55.450
And I love her.

10:55.486 --> 10:58.387
Congratulations. (CHUCKLES)

10:58.422 --> 10:59.721
We need to talk...

11:01.325 --> 11:03.725
...in, uh, in private.

11:11.168 --> 11:13.535
Already creating tension
with your soon-to-be aunt.

11:13.570 --> 11:17.539
Uncle, the Tooth Fairy
is demanding 1/3 of the money

11:17.574 --> 11:19.474
that I owe him.

11:19.510 --> 11:22.444
Look, did you see the news
with that cop who got hanged?

11:22.479 --> 11:23.879
I think Patrick did that.

11:23.914 --> 11:26.348
I swear to God, if I don't pay
him back, I'm gonna be next.

11:26.383 --> 11:29.451
How much?

11:29.486 --> 11:30.719
$200,000.

11:30.754 --> 11:33.889
Jesus, a few thousand, maybe.
But $200,000?

11:33.924 --> 11:36.525
Oh, come on, you've always got
a job lined up, right?

11:36.560 --> 11:37.893
I want in on something big.

11:37.928 --> 11:40.762
Ah. Hey, I know that look.

11:40.798 --> 11:42.864
Now whatever it is,
I wanna be a part of it.

11:42.900 --> 11:44.132
- Dion...
- Oh, come on.

11:44.168 --> 11:46.034
We stole from the wine warehouse
together, didn't we?

11:46.069 --> 11:48.069
That went like clockwork.

11:48.105 --> 11:50.305
My next job is not
some wine heist, okay?

11:52.609 --> 11:55.377
It's armed robbery,
accent on the "armed."

11:55.412 --> 11:57.512
And with you on parole, you
could get decades behind bars.

11:57.548 --> 11:59.181
Yeah, well,
I'll take that chance.

11:59.216 --> 12:01.049
Dion, you're in a good place
in your life.

12:01.084 --> 12:02.217
You're a successful chef,

12:02.252 --> 12:04.286
and more importantly,
you're about to be a father.

12:04.321 --> 12:05.520
You need to be around
for that.

12:05.556 --> 12:06.922
No, no, no,
you don't understand.

12:06.957 --> 12:08.690
The Tooth Fairy is going crazy.

12:08.725 --> 12:10.192
I gotta score some money
from somewhere.

12:10.227 --> 12:12.160
Even if I did think it was
a good idea, which I don't,

12:12.196 --> 12:13.628
I can't bring you in.

12:13.664 --> 12:16.364
Someone else is pulling this job
and he's not going to want you.

12:16.400 --> 12:18.266
You're a chef,
not a gangster.

12:18.302 --> 12:21.303
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING)

12:34.651 --> 12:37.619
Lovely bouquet.

12:37.654 --> 12:39.921
What are you doing here?

12:39.957 --> 12:41.356
Research.

12:41.391 --> 12:43.725
I'm thinking of getting back
into the restaurant business,

12:43.760 --> 12:46.428
so I'm curious as to what
other people are doing.

12:46.463 --> 12:48.630
Patrick, I'm...
I'm really busy, so...

12:48.665 --> 12:50.832
I'm sure Dion told you
that I've got my eye on

12:50.868 --> 12:53.568
an exquisite property
in Williamsburg.

12:53.604 --> 12:58.139
When I showed it to him,
he showed genuine interest,

12:58.175 --> 13:02.210
if the word "genuine" can ever
be applied to Dion Patras.

13:02.246 --> 13:04.379
I don't know why
he'd be interested.

13:04.414 --> 13:06.548
I mean, Thirio's doing great.

13:06.583 --> 13:10.652
So it would seem, which is good
for Dion's sake.

13:10.687 --> 13:12.120
And mine.

13:12.155 --> 13:14.356
Well...

13:14.391 --> 13:16.224
you don't owe me $600,000.

13:16.260 --> 13:18.894
(BOTTLE CLINKS)

13:18.929 --> 13:22.631
He shared that detail
with you, right?

13:22.666 --> 13:25.200
Yeah.

13:25.235 --> 13:28.737
I'd reconsider my alliances
if I were you,

13:28.772 --> 13:33.675
considering the financial
burden and corresponding risk.

13:33.710 --> 13:34.910
What do you mean "risk"?

13:34.945 --> 13:37.312
(INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

13:37.347 --> 13:39.347
Quiet intensity,

13:39.383 --> 13:42.817
not quite mature,
dark body.

13:42.853 --> 13:46.154
What does this make me
think of?

13:46.189 --> 13:49.190
Oh, right.

13:49.226 --> 13:50.492
Your son.

13:50.527 --> 13:53.562
Hey. This is my home.
Get out of here.

13:55.532 --> 13:57.098
Get out of here!

13:58.602 --> 14:00.435
Needs to breathe.

14:00.470 --> 14:03.471
(INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

14:09.146 --> 14:10.378
(DOOR CLOSES)

14:10.414 --> 14:11.580
(PAPERS THUD)

14:19.406 --> 14:20.406
Patrick!

14:22.977 --> 14:24.110
What are you doing here?

14:24.145 --> 14:26.412
I work here.

14:26.447 --> 14:27.646
This is your restaurant?

14:27.682 --> 14:29.448
Yeah, the one
you helped me with.

14:29.484 --> 14:32.151
What are you doing here?

14:32.186 --> 14:33.452
Business.

14:33.488 --> 14:36.355
Oh.
Uh, parking lot business?

14:36.390 --> 14:38.224
We're negotiating.
Good to see you.

14:38.259 --> 14:39.492
Is everything okay?

14:42.130 --> 14:44.530
You should probably
get back to work.

14:44.565 --> 14:46.866
I'm sure you have your hands
full running this place.

14:46.901 --> 14:50.569
I can take a break.
It'd be nice to catch up.

14:50.605 --> 14:53.873
I mean...
if <i> you</i> have time.

15:02.817 --> 15:04.817
- (VAN DOOR CLOSES)
- Is he your bodyguard?

15:04.852 --> 15:07.653
My associate.

15:09.257 --> 15:11.557
How long have you been
in this business?

15:11.592 --> 15:13.392
I grew up in it.

15:18.666 --> 15:21.967
So...

15:22.003 --> 15:25.271
how's it going with the person
you're in love with?

15:30.044 --> 15:31.677
Unrequited.

15:33.214 --> 15:36.682
Are you happy, Patrick?

15:36.717 --> 15:38.217
I have been.

15:38.252 --> 15:42.454
I enjoyed
owning a restaurant.

15:42.490 --> 15:43.689
Why not do that again?

15:43.724 --> 15:45.057
Because it doesn't line up

15:45.092 --> 15:48.160
with my father's vision
for our business.

15:48.196 --> 15:50.763
He found it... precious.

15:50.798 --> 15:52.798
That must be hard.

15:52.834 --> 15:56.869
You're a very...
sensitive person.

15:56.904 --> 16:01.740
And it sounds like your father
doesn't understand you.

16:01.776 --> 16:04.977
Why not step out
of his shadow?

16:05.012 --> 16:09.114
Be yourself and do whatever it
takes to make <i> you</i> happy?

16:12.420 --> 16:14.353
(DOOR OPENS)

16:17.024 --> 16:18.557
Hey, man.

16:18.593 --> 16:20.326
Listen, uh,
just letting you know,

16:20.361 --> 16:22.628
my uncle's getting married.
Don't ask.

16:22.663 --> 16:24.730
He wants to do it here
at Thirio.

16:24.765 --> 16:28.100
I just had a face-to-face
with Patrick Woijchik.

16:28.135 --> 16:30.469
What do you mean?
He... he was here?

16:30.504 --> 16:33.072
He said you owe him $600,000.
Is that right?

16:33.107 --> 16:34.540
It's a little more complicated
than that.

16:34.575 --> 16:37.142
So your
whole song and dance...

16:37.178 --> 16:39.945
"Do the restaurant for Rie.
Do it for T.J."

16:39.981 --> 16:41.146
It was all bullshit.

16:41.182 --> 16:43.415
- What exactly did he say to you?
- The truth.

16:43.451 --> 16:46.485
That this restaurant, that
everything we've been working on

16:46.520 --> 16:48.587
is just so you can pay off
a debt.

16:48.623 --> 16:50.756
You manipulated my feelings

16:50.791 --> 16:54.093
and you used my son
to save your own ass.

16:54.128 --> 16:56.328
There's something you gotta
understand first.

16:56.364 --> 16:58.063
If I don't find a way
of paying him back,

16:58.099 --> 16:59.398
if... if I'd have left town,

16:59.433 --> 17:02.935
he said he was gonna kill
everyone that is close to me.

17:02.970 --> 17:06.005
- Give me a break.
- Starting with you, Tommy!

17:07.308 --> 17:10.442
He said he was going to
kill you.

17:10.478 --> 17:13.012
And I couldn't
let that happen.

17:13.047 --> 17:14.946
You mean more to me
than anything.

17:14.982 --> 17:19.117
Come on, think back 25 years.

17:19.153 --> 17:20.719
My parents
had just been killed.

17:20.755 --> 17:22.688
I'm... I'm living
in my uncle's whorehouse.

17:22.723 --> 17:25.023
He's in and out of jail
most of that time.

17:25.059 --> 17:28.994
And then you come along,

17:29.030 --> 17:31.997
and you give me the one thing
that I needed...

17:32.033 --> 17:34.300
someone I could count on.

17:34.335 --> 17:36.168
You always used to say
that I helped you, you know,

17:36.203 --> 17:37.403
standing up
to those punk kids

17:37.438 --> 17:38.771
who were picking on you
at school.

17:38.806 --> 17:41.941
(VOICE BREAKING) But, no.
You... you helped me, Tommy.

17:44.578 --> 17:46.812
You... you saved my life.

17:46.847 --> 17:49.848
(SLOW TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

17:52.820 --> 17:56.021
So I can't let anybody
hurt you.

17:56.057 --> 17:57.957
I had to think of something.

17:57.992 --> 18:00.526
threatened T.J.

18:03.564 --> 18:06.398
I'm gonna fix it.

18:06.434 --> 18:08.600
I swear to God,
I'm gonna figure it out.

18:12.239 --> 18:14.373
We'll figure it out
together.

18:17.011 --> 18:20.145
- (SIGHS)
- (KNOCKS)

18:20.181 --> 18:22.081
I saw my father
this morning.

18:22.116 --> 18:24.750
He certainly seems to be back
to his feisty old self again.

18:24.785 --> 18:28.387
- Yes. He's making progress.
- Wonderful.

18:28.422 --> 18:32.057
So you'll authorize
his transfer back to prison.

18:32.093 --> 18:34.960
He's still
in serious condition,

18:34.996 --> 18:36.762
just starting to rehab
from his stroke.

18:36.797 --> 18:39.999
He'll rehab just as well
in the prison infirmary.

18:40.034 --> 18:42.868
Is that really the safest option
given what happened to him?

18:44.205 --> 18:47.172
You're not hearing me.

18:47.208 --> 18:51.577
My father is ready
to go back to prison. Now.

18:58.519 --> 19:02.688
Hey, are you going into
business with Patrick Woijchik?

19:02.723 --> 19:05.290
How do you know
Patrick Woijchik?

19:05.326 --> 19:06.525
From the hospital.

19:06.560 --> 19:08.894
Uh, my sister and his dad
were on the same floor.

19:08.929 --> 19:10.162
He helped me out

19:10.197 --> 19:11.330
when I was in a jam
with the health inspection.

19:11.365 --> 19:13.732
Helped you out how?

19:13.768 --> 19:16.368
He made a call.
He has connections.

19:16.404 --> 19:19.938
Okay,
about those connections...

19:19.974 --> 19:21.940
There's a rougher side
to Patrick's business

19:21.976 --> 19:23.208
that you may not know about.

19:23.244 --> 19:25.010
I kind of do know
about that.

19:25.046 --> 19:27.579
I also know he's passionate
about restaurants.

19:27.615 --> 19:29.548
Pilar, he's a criminal.

19:29.583 --> 19:31.750
Just... you should stay away
from him.

19:31.786 --> 19:33.952
I'm telling you, there's more
to him than you know.

19:33.988 --> 19:36.388
He could do more for us.

19:36.424 --> 19:37.823
I think it'd be good
for both of you.

19:37.858 --> 19:39.191
Okay, you really don't know

19:39.226 --> 19:40.492
what you're talking about
right now.

19:40.528 --> 19:42.127
I do.
He's smart and he's savvy...

19:42.163 --> 19:44.830
Pilar, I've got a lot of crap
I'm dealing with,

19:44.865 --> 19:46.999
and Patrick's at the top
of that list.

19:47.034 --> 19:48.967
I get it. You think you know
what's good for me,

19:49.003 --> 19:51.270
but you're wrong.

19:51.305 --> 19:53.072
I'm just trying to help.

19:57.244 --> 20:01.647
(SLOW-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING)

20:01.682 --> 20:05.484
(CITY AMBIENCE, HORNS HONKING )

20:08.255 --> 20:10.522
(LINE RINGS)

20:10.558 --> 20:12.357
<i>Hi, you've reached
Marisa Gallo.</i>

20:12.393 --> 20:14.560
<i>- Please leave a message.
- (BEEP)</i>

20:14.595 --> 20:16.195
Hey.

20:16.230 --> 20:20.365
So I guess you're not gonna
answer my calls.

20:20.401 --> 20:24.236
(SIGHS) Look...

20:24.271 --> 20:27.139
I wanna be a part of your life.

20:27.174 --> 20:29.074
And if I can't have that,

20:29.110 --> 20:32.544
then I at least wanna be
a father to our kid.

20:32.580 --> 20:34.780
So, uh...

20:34.815 --> 20:37.082
you know, just...
just letting you know that.

20:41.388 --> 20:43.856
Well, the sooner the better
for me.

20:43.891 --> 20:46.125
Great. I'll see you then.

20:48.429 --> 20:49.928
What's going on?

20:49.964 --> 20:51.230
I have T.J. today.

20:51.265 --> 20:53.065
You think I'm gonna let him
set foot in your house

20:53.100 --> 20:54.399
after what you did?

20:54.435 --> 20:55.734
Forget it.

20:55.769 --> 20:58.237
I've changed the locks
on all my gun boxes.

20:58.272 --> 20:59.371
Won't happen again.

20:59.406 --> 21:00.739
Damn right
it won't happen again

21:00.774 --> 21:02.508
'cause I'm not letting him
near you anymore.

21:02.543 --> 21:03.909
Do you understand?

21:03.944 --> 21:05.377
Somebody could've been killed.

21:05.412 --> 21:08.013
Fine.
We won't go to my house.

21:08.048 --> 21:10.115
I'll pick him up later,
take him for a bite to eat,

21:10.151 --> 21:11.917
and then we'll go straight
to the art show.

21:11.952 --> 21:13.318
Does that meet with
your approval?

21:13.354 --> 21:14.653
What? He invited you
to the art show?

21:14.688 --> 21:16.955
Of course he did.

21:16.991 --> 21:18.724
Kid's crazy about me.

21:20.461 --> 21:22.594
I'm sorry. I can't.

21:22.630 --> 21:25.864
Thomas.

21:25.900 --> 21:29.134
Being with that boy
is my one pleasure in life.

21:30.871 --> 21:35.741
Decades of radio silence
and now this.

21:35.776 --> 21:37.109
This isn't you.

21:37.144 --> 21:40.445
It's the me I am now.

21:40.481 --> 21:42.881
You get to my age,
you see the end of the road.

21:42.917 --> 21:45.417
Are you sick, Aidan?

21:45.452 --> 21:48.287
Nah. I'm old.

21:48.322 --> 21:50.556
Got issues,
some of them not good.

21:52.226 --> 21:54.393
You gonna let me take him
or what?

21:56.730 --> 21:59.064
Just this once. I'm not
committing to anything.

21:59.099 --> 22:00.699
God forbid.

22:00.734 --> 22:03.335
- Hey, T.J.!
- And just so you know,

22:03.370 --> 22:05.070
T.J. and I are going down
to the school tomorrow

22:05.105 --> 22:06.905
and telling them the truth
about that gun.

22:06.941 --> 22:08.240
Are you out of your mind?

22:08.275 --> 22:09.942
You got your set of morals,
I got mine.

22:09.977 --> 22:12.644
- Yeah, well, your morals are...
- (FOOTSTEPS DESCENDING)

22:12.680 --> 22:19.785
Hey! There he is.
(CHUCKLES)

22:19.820 --> 22:20.953
We'll go get pizza later,

22:20.988 --> 22:22.221
then I'll take you
to the art show,

22:22.256 --> 22:24.056
All right, kid?

22:24.091 --> 22:26.792
We'll talk later.

22:33.100 --> 22:37.402
(TWANGY MUSIC PLAYING)

22:40.140 --> 22:43.108
So we will set up the band
over there.

22:43.143 --> 22:44.276
And, of course,
we'll need a dance floor.

22:44.311 --> 22:45.777
TASHA: Yeah, a big one.

22:45.813 --> 22:46.979
She's right.

22:47.014 --> 22:48.180
We can't have people
crashing into each other

22:48.215 --> 22:50.349
when they're dancing <i> hasapiko.</i>
Ha ha!

22:50.384 --> 22:51.717
Hey, T.J.

22:53.554 --> 22:54.953
<i>Hey, T.J.!</i>

22:54.989 --> 22:57.155
<i>(TIRES SQUEAL, RIE SCREAMS)</i>

22:57.191 --> 22:58.523
<i>T.J.: No!</i>

23:03.197 --> 23:06.164
And then we'll need
one huge table

23:06.200 --> 23:09.201
which is where we put the goat.

23:09.236 --> 23:10.769
Goat?

23:10.804 --> 23:12.037
He wants me to cook a goat.

23:12.072 --> 23:13.505
- TASHA: Make it two goats.
- STAVROS: Oh.

23:13.540 --> 23:15.574
40 people, 20 a goat.

23:15.609 --> 23:18.744
Okay, why don't we all sit down
and make a list?

23:18.779 --> 23:20.512
Food. Wine.

23:20.547 --> 23:21.713
Animals.

23:21.749 --> 23:24.216
It's a great idea. You...

23:24.251 --> 23:26.818
you guys do a list.

23:29.723 --> 23:31.790
Look, what the hell are
you doing here?

23:31.825 --> 23:33.525
You can't expect a third
so soon.

23:33.560 --> 23:36.461
Why do you always assume
it's all about you, Dion?

23:36.497 --> 23:38.196
Patrick.

23:38.232 --> 23:39.998
Thanks for stopping by.

23:40.034 --> 23:42.634
Uh, why don't we go into
the office?

23:46.440 --> 23:48.807
Hey, wait a minute.
What the hell is going on here?

23:48.842 --> 23:51.043
We have a problem.
I have a solution.

23:51.078 --> 23:54.746
(INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

23:54.782 --> 23:57.149
Five minutes. Okay?

23:58.519 --> 24:00.118
(WHISPERING) Hey, hey?

24:05.785 --> 24:08.320
Thank you for your time.

24:08.356 --> 24:10.923
Obviously, we are eager
to relieve Dion

24:10.958 --> 24:12.491
of the debt he owes you.

24:12.527 --> 24:14.827
So we're prepared
to offer you

24:14.862 --> 24:16.495
one-quarter interest
in Thirio.

24:16.531 --> 24:18.397
- Tommy, what...
- Really?

24:18.432 --> 24:22.735
You'd forfeit 25% of your stake
to cover Dion's screw-up?

24:22.770 --> 24:24.036
What a good friend.

24:24.071 --> 24:25.604
All right, let's just hang on
a minute here.

24:25.640 --> 24:26.839
No, this... this is
not something

24:26.874 --> 24:28.107
Tommy and I
have fully discussed.

24:28.142 --> 24:30.876
Well, we'll fully discuss it
after we have an answer.

24:30.912 --> 24:32.878
Patrick.

24:32.914 --> 24:35.147
I am...

24:35.182 --> 24:36.348
very interested.

24:36.384 --> 24:38.417
No, no, no, no.
Stop, stop, stop.

24:38.452 --> 24:39.852
Look, I owe you cash,

24:39.887 --> 24:43.188
not a stake in the restaurant
that's an iffy venture at best.

24:43.224 --> 24:44.924
Your partner just offered me
a percentage.

24:44.959 --> 24:46.859
I absolutely did.
I'll have our manager...

24:46.894 --> 24:48.727
- I am so sorry. No, no.
- ...draw up a contract.

24:48.763 --> 24:50.462
A stake in Thirio?

24:50.498 --> 24:52.364
- It's off the table.
- It's not off the table.

24:52.400 --> 24:55.100
It's dangerous for a person
to tell me no. But twice?

24:55.136 --> 24:56.287
We're not telling you no.
I'm not telling you no.

24:56.312 --> 24:57.069
Patrick, I will pay you back.

24:57.104 --> 24:57.907
Just... just give me a
chance to talk to him.

24:57.933 --> 24:58.572
Tommy just has his wires crossed.

24:58.606 --> 25:00.673
(SPEAKING OVER EACH OTHER)

25:00.708 --> 25:02.541
If this is how the two of you
do business,

25:02.577 --> 25:04.009
I worry about your future.

25:06.047 --> 25:08.380
- What are you doing?
- Well, T, I appreciate the gesture,

25:08.416 --> 25:10.816
but we do not want to get in
business with Patrick Woijchik.

25:10.851 --> 25:12.151
You forget,

25:12.186 --> 25:15.220
I grew up with guys like that
in my living room. All right?

25:15.256 --> 25:18.324
(CONVERSATION CONTINUES
INDISTINCTLY)

25:23.431 --> 25:25.998
I wish you both
a long and happy life together.

25:27.602 --> 25:31.537
Sad that your nephew won't
be around to share it with you.

25:31.572 --> 25:33.672
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION
CONTINUES)

25:33.708 --> 25:35.374
Yeah, well, you can't make
a guy like that happy.

25:35.409 --> 25:36.742
That's not how it works.

25:36.777 --> 25:38.877
Well, he's definitely
not happy now.

25:38.913 --> 25:42.781
Uh, Uncle, could I, uh,
could I have a minute, please?

25:48.522 --> 25:49.888
Man, I am begging you.

25:49.924 --> 25:53.025
You gotta talk to your guy
about letting me in on that job.

25:53.060 --> 25:54.996
Look, the Tooth Fairy's
going off the rails...

25:55.021 --> 25:55.861
There is no guy.

25:55.896 --> 25:58.263
I told you that because I wanted
to protect you.

25:58.299 --> 26:00.232
It's my job
and it's dangerous, but...

26:00.267 --> 26:02.267
But what?

26:02.303 --> 26:03.469
Maybe not as dangerous

26:03.504 --> 26:06.538
as being on the wrong side
of that crazy Polack.

26:06.574 --> 26:07.740
So I'm in?

26:09.343 --> 26:11.910
All right, great. Come on,
tell me. Tell me, what is it?

26:11.946 --> 26:13.912
One of my girls has a cousin
who bartends

26:13.948 --> 26:15.881
at one of these
high stakes poker games.

26:15.916 --> 26:18.917
Hundreds of thousands of dollars
on the table, all cash.

26:18.953 --> 26:20.252
Nice. That's what
I'm talking about.

26:20.287 --> 26:22.621
Be at my place at 7:00.

26:22.657 --> 26:23.922
Tonight.

26:26.093 --> 26:29.094
(INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING)

26:38.239 --> 26:41.240
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

26:45.579 --> 26:47.346
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

26:56.490 --> 26:58.290
- (KNOCKS)
- Yo, T.

26:58.325 --> 27:00.926
- Hey.
- Hey.

27:00.961 --> 27:02.561
Look, uh, I just wanted
to let you know

27:02.596 --> 27:04.797
I'm not gonna be able to make it
T.J.'s art show tonight.

27:04.832 --> 27:06.365
Why not?

27:06.400 --> 27:08.701
Well, I just gotta
take care of somethin'.

27:08.736 --> 27:10.502
"Something"?

27:10.538 --> 27:12.638
Well, you.

27:12.673 --> 27:13.872
T.J.

27:15.710 --> 27:17.710
All of us.

27:17.745 --> 27:19.978
What are you gonna do?

27:20.014 --> 27:23.615
It's gonna help us out,
man.

27:23.651 --> 27:27.753
Dion, there's no legal way
you can get $200,000 tonight.

27:27.788 --> 27:31.323
Tell T.J. I'm sorry
and, uh...

27:31.358 --> 27:34.760
and I'll make it up to him,
all right?

27:34.795 --> 27:36.328
Hey.

27:36.363 --> 27:39.031
Don't do something stupid
like getting killed.

27:39.066 --> 27:40.733
No, I won't.

27:40.768 --> 27:42.601
Just if anyone gets to kill you,
it should be me.

27:42.636 --> 27:44.203
(CHUCKLES)

27:44.238 --> 27:46.672
Yeah. Yeah.

27:46.707 --> 27:48.741
Right.

27:48.776 --> 27:52.010
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING)

27:54.482 --> 27:57.750
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

27:57.785 --> 27:58.951
Thirio.

27:58.986 --> 28:00.686
Oh, good. You're, uh,
you're still there.

28:00.721 --> 28:04.022
<i>Yeah, um, some stuff
for tomorrow.</i>

28:04.058 --> 28:07.860
<i>I've been, um, I've been
thinking a lot about you.</i>

28:07.895 --> 28:10.095
About how I never know what
I'm talking about?

28:10.131 --> 28:12.131
(CHUCKLES)

28:12.166 --> 28:14.933
No. Um...

28:14.969 --> 28:17.770
About how we've never
gotten a coffee.

28:17.805 --> 28:20.606
Or gone on a walk,

28:20.641 --> 28:23.308
let alone
had a proper date.

28:23.344 --> 28:25.511
And I'd really like
to do something about that.

28:25.546 --> 28:28.514
(TENDER MUSIC PLAYING)

28:31.552 --> 28:33.185
God, I love that smile.

28:35.756 --> 28:38.023
- (LAUGHS)
- (LAUGHS)

28:39.794 --> 28:41.460
You should call more often.

28:43.831 --> 28:45.030
Hey, do you wanna go

28:45.065 --> 28:47.533
to T.J.'s art thing
with me tonight?

28:47.568 --> 28:48.734
I don't know.

28:48.769 --> 28:50.569
I mean, should our first
official date

28:50.604 --> 28:52.237
be at T.J.'s school function?

28:53.707 --> 28:56.742
Well, I think it would mean
a lot to him if you were there.

28:56.777 --> 28:59.378
I know it would mean
a lot to me.

28:59.413 --> 29:01.079
All right.

29:01.115 --> 29:03.682
Yeah. Let's go.

29:03.717 --> 29:07.085
Great. I'll, uh,
I'll pick you up...

29:07.121 --> 29:09.922
Now. Yeah? (LAUGHS)

29:09.957 --> 29:11.957
(LAUGHS)

29:11.992 --> 29:14.193
(RECEIVER CLATTERS)

29:14.228 --> 29:15.794
AIDAN: Not bad, kid.

29:15.830 --> 29:17.296
Looks just like
the real thing.

29:17.331 --> 29:18.797
All it needs
is a decent frame.

29:18.833 --> 29:21.600
We'll get one next time
you come over, huh?

29:25.172 --> 29:26.672
TOMMY: Wow.

29:26.707 --> 29:28.207
This is gonna be cool.

29:28.242 --> 29:30.108
PILAR: (CHUCKLES)
Oh, my God.

29:30.144 --> 29:32.878
Hey, there he is!
Man of the hour.

29:32.913 --> 29:35.147
How are you, buddy?
Look who I brought.

29:35.182 --> 29:37.482
Are you kidding? Wild horses
couldn't keep me away.

29:37.518 --> 29:40.919
All right, lead us to
the T.J. Moran gallery.

29:46.861 --> 29:50.195
Is this...
is this all you?

29:50.231 --> 29:52.064
Oh, my God!

29:52.099 --> 29:53.699
Oh, look at
that great bridge!

29:53.734 --> 29:55.133
That's the Whitestone, right?

29:55.169 --> 29:57.636
Wow.

29:57.671 --> 30:00.239
Oh, Dion wanted to be here,
but, um, some, uh,

30:00.274 --> 30:02.507
last-minute kitchen business
came up.

30:02.543 --> 30:05.110
But we're here, right?

30:05.145 --> 30:06.545
Yeah.

30:06.580 --> 30:08.080
Wow, look at the house.

30:08.115 --> 30:09.648
PILAR: And <i> we</i> vote these

30:09.683 --> 30:11.917
the best pictures
in the whole show.

30:13.287 --> 30:15.187
Hey, um,

30:15.222 --> 30:16.355
why don't you
show Pilar around,

30:16.390 --> 30:17.689
and I'll catch up
with you guys, huh?

30:17.725 --> 30:19.892
Yeah?

30:25.132 --> 30:27.900
I need to talk to you
for a minute. It's important.

30:36.577 --> 30:41.079
(SIGHS) Make it quick.
I've had my fill of kiddie art.

30:41.115 --> 30:45.517
Dion got us into some bad
business that involves some...

30:45.552 --> 30:47.085
Some dangerous elements.

30:47.121 --> 30:48.954
Speak English.
Who we talking about?

30:48.989 --> 30:51.723
The Woijchiks.

30:51.759 --> 30:53.458
Dion's a crazier bastard
than I thought

30:53.494 --> 30:56.495
if he got on the wrong side
of that family.

30:56.530 --> 30:59.665
Problem is, now <i> I'm</i> involved,

30:59.700 --> 31:01.900
and it's put T.J. in danger.

31:01.936 --> 31:03.835
What the hell
you talking about?

